reviewText: the grapevine release isn't great but it appears to be all that's out there.  if you want the movie, get it as it is watchable.

Honestly, I bought this DVD souly for the "Rowdy Ann" short feature which stars my cousin Fay Tincher. She was called the Female Charlie Chaplin of her day and it is very difficult to find any of her works on DVD and so I jumped at the chance to get this DVD.
